The KwaDukuza Regional Court on Friday convicted and sentenced a 40 year-old man to 30 years imprisonment for raping his niece in 2012.Major General Bheki Langa, the KwaZulu-Natal Acting Provincial Commissioner welcomed the strong sentence handed down to the uncle saying that this will be a caution to those committing gender based crimes.&#8220;This will send a strong message to the would-be rapists who think of committing such crimes. We are putting extra efforts commitments when dealing with such crimes against women and children,&#8221; he said.The uncle is accused to have repeatedly raped the woman who was mentally ill over the period while she was staying with the uncle and his wife at their home in Hlomendlini. However she did not report the matter to anyone until she became pregnant.It is after the pregnancy that family members questioned her and she told them that her uncle impregnated her. A case of rape was opened at the Newark police station.The KwaDukuza Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit took over the investigation into the case and the accused was later arrested. DNA evidence linked him to the case and led to the successful conviction of a 30 year imprisonment.-TNA Reporter &nbsp;